														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1628776">
									

<p>I love these logs. I tend to enjoy overexplained SCPs though, but it seems like others like it too.</p>
<p>My one problem here, and with many other pages involving D-class dialogue, is that they sound way too clinical and formal at times. Certainly a far cry from the staff's dialogue, but I would think that people scooped up out of death row or hobos off the streets wouldn't sound so&#8230;educated, and disciplined. I do realize that D-class are more of an in-universe convenience than anything, but I recently read the Cabinet Labyrinth (or whatever it's called) just a little ways back from this one in the list and its logs gave each D-class a small description including a bit of background and temperament. It was fantastic, and I think other articles could benefit from similar tidbits.</p>
<p>All that rant aside, I'm one that always sees room for improvement and I tend to emphasize that more than what I like about something. I could probably write many times more regarding what I like about this SCP. And with that, I'll step off my soapbox.</p>

